Ext.data.JsonP['Titanium_UI_AlertDialog']({"tagname":"class","name":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","extends":"Titanium.Proxy","mixins":[],"alternateClassNames":[],"aliases":{},"singleton":false,"requires":[],"uses":[],"enum":null,"override":null,"inheritable":null,"inheritdoc":null,"meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8"],"editurl":"https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_mobile/edit/master/apidoc/Titanium/UI/AlertDialog.yml","description":["<table id=\"platformComparison\">\n  <tr>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_android.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_ios.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_mobileweb.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr><th>Android</th><th>iOS</th><th>Mobile Web</th></tr>\n</table>\n\n<p>An alert dialog is created using {@link Titanium.UI#method-createAlertDialog} or <strong><code>&lt;AlertDialog&gt;</code></strong> Alloy element.</p>\n\n<p>Although this dialog always appears in the middle of the display (not touching the edges), \nother aspects of its aesthetics and the way the user interacts with it are different for each \nplatform, as described below.</p>\n\n<h4>Android</h4>\n\n<p>On Android, the default alert dialog displays text information, via a title and message, without \nany buttons. As the user can use the system hardware <code>back</code> button to dismiss it, a button is \noptional.</p>\n\n<p>Buttons are shown if the <code>buttonNames</code> property is defined, and are rendered horizontally below \nthe message.</p>\n\n<p>To create a custom layout, a view may be added and, in turn, a hierarchy of views added to that \nchild view.</p>\n\n<h4>iOS</h4>\n\n<p>On iOS, the default alert dialog displays text information, via a title and message, with \na single button to allow it to be dismissed.</p>\n\n<p>Buttons are defined using the <code>buttonNames</code> property and are rendered vertically below \nthe message.</p>\n\n<p>On iOS 4.0 and later, alert dialogs are automatically cancelled when the application is \npaused/suspended. This behavior can avoided by setting <code>persistent</code> property on alert dialog \nto be <code>true</code>.</p>\n\n<p>On iOS 5.0 and later, <code>style</code> property can be used to allow the user to enter plain text, \nobscured text or login identifier and password. Entered values can be captured with listening\n<code>cancel</code> event.</p>\n\n<h4>Global Alias</h4>\n\n<p>A global method <code>alert()</code> is aliased to this object, and can be invoked with a single message. \nFor example</p>\n\n<pre><code>alert('this is a message');\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will generate an alert with a title of \"Alert\" and an \"OK\" button.</p>\n\n<h4>Caveats</h4>\n\n<p>Multiple alerts should not be shown at once.</p>\n\n<p>The <code>title</code> and <code>ok</code> properties cannot be changed while the alert dialog is being displayed. On\nAndroid only, you can change the <code>message</code> property while the alert dialog is being displayed.</p> \n<h3>Examples</h3>\n<h4>Single-button Alert Dialog (using alias)</h4>\n<p>Create a single-button alert dialog using the global <code>alert()</code> alias.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\n  exitOnClose: true,\n  fullscreen: false\n});\n\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  alert('The file has been deleted');\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre><h4>Single-button Alert Dialog (standard)</h4>\n<p>Create a single-button alert dialog, without explicitly defining it using the <code>buttonNames</code> \nproperty, which is invoked when the app window is clicked.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\nexitOnClose: true,\nfullscreen: false\n});\n\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    message: 'The file has been deleted',\n    ok: 'Okay',\n    title: 'File Deleted'\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre><h4>Three-button Alert Dialog</h4>\n<p>Create a three-button alert dialog, which is invoked when the app window is clicked. \nOutput a message to the log when the cancel button is clicked.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\n  exitOnClose: true,\n  fullscreen: false\n});\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    cancel: 1,\n    buttonNames: ['Confirm', 'Cancel', 'Help'],\n    message: 'Would you like to delete the file?',\n    title: 'Delete'\n  });\n  dialog.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n    if (e.index === e.source.cancel){\n      Ti.API.info('The cancel button was clicked');\n    }\n    Ti.API.info('e.cancel: ' + e.cancel);\n    Ti.API.info('e.source.cancel: ' + e.source.cancel);\n    Ti.API.info('e.index: ' + e.index);\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre><h4>Alert Dialog with Plain Text Input (iOS 5 and later)</h4>\n<p>Create an alert dialog and allow the user enter plain text, which is invoked when the\napp window is clicked.\nOutput entered text value to the log when the OK button is clicked.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({\n  title: 'Click window to test'\n});\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    title: 'Enter text',\n    style: Ti.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.PLAIN_TEXT_INPUT,\n    buttonNames: ['OK']\n  });\n  dialog.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n    Ti.API.info('e.text: ' + e.text);\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre><h4>Alloy XML Markup</h4>\n<p>Previous three-button alert dialog example as an Alloy view.</p>\n\n<p>alertdialog.xml:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Alloy&gt;\n    &lt;Window id=\"win\" onClick=\"showDialog\" title=\"Click window to test\" backgroundColor=\"white\"\n        exitOnClose=\"true\" fullscreen=\"false\" &gt;\n\n        &lt;AlertDialog id=\"dialog\" onClick=\"doClick\" title=\"Delete\"\n            message=\"Would you like to delete the file?\" cancel=\"1\"&gt;\n\n            &lt;!-- The ButtonNames tag sets the buttonNames property. --&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonNames&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Confirm&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Cancel&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Help&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;/ButtonNames&gt;\n        &lt;/AlertDialog&gt;\n    &lt;/Window&gt;\n&lt;/Alloy&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>alertdialog.js:</p>\n\n<pre><code>function showDialog(){\n    $.dialog.show();\n};\n\nfunction doClick(e){\n    Ti.API.info('e.text: ' + e.text);\n};\n</code></pre>"]},"private":null,"id":"class-Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","members":{"cfg":[],"property":[{"name":"androidView","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>In an Alloy application you can specify this property with either an <code>&lt;AndroidView/&gt;</code> or\n<code>&lt;View/&gt;</code> element inside the <code>&lt;AlertDialog/&gt;</code> element, for example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Alloy&gt;\n    &lt;AlertDialog onClick=\"doClick\" title=\"Delete\"\n        message=\"Would you like to delete the file?\" cancel=\"1\"&gt;\n\n        &lt;!--  Add View or AndroidView for the androidView property  --&gt;\n        &lt;View platform=\"android\"&gt;\n            &lt;Label color=\"red\" text=\"Warning!  This change is permanent and you cannot undo it!\" /&gt;\n        &lt;/View&gt;\n\n        &lt;ButtonNames&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Confirm&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Cancel&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n        &lt;/ButtonNames&gt;\n    &lt;/AlertDialog&gt;\n&lt;/Alloy&gt;\n</code></pre>"],"platform":["android 0.8"]},"id":"property-androidView"},{"name":"apiName","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"readonly":true,"description":["<p>The value of this property is the fully qualified name of the API. For example, {@link Titanium.UI.Button Button}\nreturns <code>Ti.UI.Button</code>.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.2.0","iphone 3.2.0","ipad 3.2.0","mobileweb 3.2.0"]},"id":"property-apiName"},{"name":"bubbleParent","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>Some proxies (most commonly views) have a relationship to other proxies, often\nestablished by the add() method. For example, for a button added to a window, a\nclick event on the button would bubble up to the window. Other common parents are\ntable sections to their rows, table views to their sections, and scrollable views\nto their views. Set this property to false to disable the bubbling to the proxy's parent.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"property-bubbleParent"},{"name":"buttonNames","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>On iOS, a button will automatically be created if none are explicitly defined, because \nwithout it users would be unable to dismiss the dialog. Conversely, a dialog with no \nbuttons may be created on Android, as the hardware <code>back</code> button may be used instead.</p>\n\n<p>A maximum of 3 buttons is supported on Android.</p>\n\n<p>Alloy applications can specify this property with a <code>&lt;ButtonNames&gt;</code> element containing\none or more <code>&lt;ButtonName&gt;</code> elements (see example).</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Alloy&gt;\n    &lt;AlertDialog id=\"dialog\" onClick=\"doClick\" title=\"Decide!\" message=\"Do you really want to do that?\" cancel=\"1\"&gt;\n        &lt;ButtonNames&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Confirm&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Cancel&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Help&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n        &lt;/ButtonNames&gt;\n    &lt;/AlertDialog&gt;\n&lt;/Alloy&gt;\n</code></pre>"]},"id":"property-buttonNames"},{"name":"cancel","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>On iOS and Mobile Web, set to <code>-1</code> to disable the cancel option.</p>"]},"id":"property-cancel"},{"name":"destructive","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>Note that this property is only available on iOS 8 or above. Setting to -1 disables this option.</p>"],"platform":["iphone 3.5.0","ipad 3.5.0"]},"id":"property-destructive"},{"name":"lifecycleContainer","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>If this property is set to a Window or TabGroup, then the corresponding Activity lifecycle event callbacks\nwill also be called on the proxy. Proxies that require the activity lifecycle will need this property set\nto the appropriate containing Window or TabGroup.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.6.0"]},"id":"property-lifecycleContainer"},{"name":"message","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"property-message"},{"name":"messageid","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"property-messageid"},{"name":"ok","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>This property is useful when only one button is required, as it negates the need to define \nthe <code>buttonNames</code> property. If <code>buttonNames</code> is defined, this property is ignored.</p>"]},"id":"property-ok"},{"name":"okid","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>If <code>buttonNames</code> is defined, this property is ignored.</p>"],"platform":["iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8"]},"id":"property-okid"},{"name":"persistent","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>This property is useful to ensure that the alert dialog will not be ignored \nby the user when the application is paused/suspended.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"property-persistent"},{"name":"style","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>Style of the alert dialog, specified using one of the constants from\n{@link Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle}. Using styles other than default one can break\nyour dialog layout if more than two buttons used. All styles can handle up to two\nbuttons comfortably, except for default style can handle up to six buttons when <code>title</code>\nand <code>message</code> is empty or not given. Note that this property is only available on\niOS SDK 5 or above. </p>"],"platform":["iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"property-style"},{"name":"title","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"description":["<p>If not set, a dialog with no title bar will be created.</p>"]},"id":"property-title"},{"name":"titleid","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"property-titleid"}],"method":[{"name":"addEventListener","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{},"id":"method-addEventListener"},{"name":"applyProperties","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>Properties are supplied as a dictionary. Each key-value pair in the object is applied to the proxy such that\nmyproxy[key] = value.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0","mobileweb 3.0.0"]},"id":"method-applyProperties"},{"name":"fireEvent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{},"id":"method-fireEvent"},{"name":"getApiName","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.2.0","iphone 3.2.0","ipad 3.2.0","mobileweb 3.2.0"]},"id":"method-getApiName"},{"name":"getBubbleParent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"method-getBubbleParent"},{"name":"getButtonNames","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-getButtonNames"},{"name":"getCancel","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-getCancel"},{"name":"getDestructive","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"platform":["iphone 3.5.0","ipad 3.5.0"]},"id":"method-getDestructive"},{"name":"getLifecycleContainer","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.6.0"]},"id":"method-getLifecycleContainer"},{"name":"getMessage","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-getMessage"},{"name":"getOk","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-getOk"},{"name":"getPersistent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"method-getPersistent"},{"name":"getStyle","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"platform":["iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"method-getStyle"},{"name":"getTitle","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-getTitle"},{"name":"hide","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-hide"},{"name":"removeEventListener","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>Multiple listeners can be registered for the same event, so the \n<code>callback</code> parameter is used to determine which listener to remove. </p>\n\n<p>When adding a listener, you must save a reference to the callback function\nin order to remove the listener later:</p>\n\n<pre><code>var listener = function() { Ti.API.info(\"Event listener called.\"); }\nwindow.addEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>To remove the listener, pass in a reference to the callback function:</p>\n\n<pre><code>window.removeEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>"]},"id":"method-removeEventListener"},{"name":"setBubbleParent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"method-setBubbleParent"},{"name":"setButtonNames","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-setButtonNames"},{"name":"setCancel","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-setCancel"},{"name":"setDestructive","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"platform":["iphone 3.5.0","ipad 3.5.0"]},"id":"method-setDestructive"},{"name":"setLifecycleContainer","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.6.0"]},"id":"method-setLifecycleContainer"},{"name":"setMessage","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-setMessage"},{"name":"setOk","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-setOk"},{"name":"setPersistent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"method-setPersistent"},{"name":"setStyle","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{"platform":["iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0"]},"id":"method-setStyle"},{"name":"setTitle","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-setTitle"},{"name":"show","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"method-show"}],"event":[{"name":"click","tagname":"event","owner":"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog","meta":{},"id":"event-click"}],"css_var":[],"css_mixin":[]},"linenr":95426,"files":[{"filename":"titanium.js","href":"titanium.html#Titanium-UI-AlertDialog"}],"html_meta":{"platform":"<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li></ul>","editurl":null,"description":"<p><table id=\"platformComparison\">\n  <tr>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_android.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_ios.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_mobileweb.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr><th>Android</th><th>iOS</th><th>Mobile Web</th></tr>\n</table>\n\n\n\n\n<p>An alert dialog is created using <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI-method-createAlertDialog\" rel=\"Titanium.UI-method-createAlertDialog\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.createAlertDialog</a> or <strong><code>&lt;AlertDialog&gt;</code></strong> Alloy element.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Although this dialog always appears in the middle of the display (not touching the edges), \nother aspects of its aesthetics and the way the user interacts with it are different for each \nplatform, as described below.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Android</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On Android, the default alert dialog displays text information, via a title and message, without \nany buttons. As the user can use the system hardware <code>back</code> button to dismiss it, a button is \noptional.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Buttons are shown if the <code>buttonNames</code> property is defined, and are rendered horizontally below \nthe message.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>To create a custom layout, a view may be added and, in turn, a hierarchy of views added to that \nchild view.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>iOS</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On iOS, the default alert dialog displays text information, via a title and message, with \na single button to allow it to be dismissed.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Buttons are defined using the <code>buttonNames</code> property and are rendered vertically below \nthe message.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On iOS 4.0 and later, alert dialogs are automatically cancelled when the application is \npaused/suspended. This behavior can avoided by setting <code>persistent</code> property on alert dialog \nto be <code>true</code>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On iOS 5.0 and later, <code>style</code> property can be used to allow the user to enter plain text, \nobscured text or login identifier and password. Entered values can be captured with listening\n<code>cancel</code> event.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Global Alias</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>A global method <code>alert()</code> is aliased to this object, and can be invoked with a single message. \nFor example</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>alert('this is a message');\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n\n<p>This will generate an alert with a title of \"Alert\" and an \"OK\" button.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Caveats</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Multiple alerts should not be shown at once.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <code>title</code> and <code>ok</code> properties cannot be changed while the alert dialog is being displayed. On\nAndroid only, you can change the <code>message</code> property while the alert dialog is being displayed.</p>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n<h3>Examples</h3>\n\n\n<h4>Single-button Alert Dialog (using alias)</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create a single-button alert dialog using the global <code>alert()</code> alias.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\n  exitOnClose: true,\n  fullscreen: false\n});\n\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  alert('The file has been deleted');\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Single-button Alert Dialog (standard)</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create a single-button alert dialog, without explicitly defining it using the <code>buttonNames</code> \nproperty, which is invoked when the app window is clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\nexitOnClose: true,\nfullscreen: false\n});\n\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    message: 'The file has been deleted',\n    ok: 'Okay',\n    title: 'File Deleted'\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Three-button Alert Dialog</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create a three-button alert dialog, which is invoked when the app window is clicked. \nOutput a message to the log when the cancel button is clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\n  exitOnClose: true,\n  fullscreen: false\n});\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    cancel: 1,\n    buttonNames: ['Confirm', 'Cancel', 'Help'],\n    message: 'Would you like to delete the file?',\n    title: 'Delete'\n  });\n  dialog.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n    if (e.index === e.source.cancel){\n      Ti.API.info('The cancel button was clicked');\n    }\n    Ti.API.info('e.cancel: ' + e.cancel);\n    Ti.API.info('e.source.cancel: ' + e.source.cancel);\n    Ti.API.info('e.index: ' + e.index);\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Alert Dialog with Plain Text Input (iOS 5 and later)</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create an alert dialog and allow the user enter plain text, which is invoked when the\napp window is clicked.\nOutput entered text value to the log when the OK button is clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({\n  title: 'Click window to test'\n});\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    title: 'Enter text',\n    style: Ti.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.PLAIN_TEXT_INPUT,\n    buttonNames: ['OK']\n  });\n  dialog.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n    Ti.API.info('e.text: ' + e.text);\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Alloy XML Markup</h4>\n\n\n<p>Previous three-button alert dialog example as an Alloy view.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>alertdialog.xml:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Alloy&gt;\n    &lt;Window id=\"win\" onClick=\"showDialog\" title=\"Click window to test\" backgroundColor=\"white\"\n        exitOnClose=\"true\" fullscreen=\"false\" &gt;\n\n        &lt;AlertDialog id=\"dialog\" onClick=\"doClick\" title=\"Delete\"\n            message=\"Would you like to delete the file?\" cancel=\"1\"&gt;\n\n            &lt;!-- The ButtonNames tag sets the buttonNames property. --&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonNames&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Confirm&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Cancel&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Help&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;/ButtonNames&gt;\n        &lt;/AlertDialog&gt;\n    &lt;/Window&gt;\n&lt;/Alloy&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n\n<p>alertdialog.js:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>function showDialog(){\n    $.dialog.show();\n};\n\nfunction doClick(e){\n    Ti.API.info('e.text: ' + e.text);\n};\n</code></pre>\n\n</p>"},"statics":{"cfg":[],"property":[],"method":[],"event":[],"css_var":[],"css_mixin":[]},"component":false,"superclasses":["Titanium.Proxy","Titanium.UI.AlertDialog"],"subclasses":[],"mixedInto":[],"parentMixins":[],"html":"<div><div class='sidebar'><ul class=\"sidebar-platforms\"><li class='platform-android' title='Android since Titanium SDK 0.8'>Android 0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone since Titanium SDK 0.8'>iPhone 0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad since Titanium SDK 0.8'>iPad 0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb' title='Mobile Web since Titanium SDK 1.8'>Mobile Web 1.8</li></ul></div><div class='hierarchy'><div class='classes'><div class='subclass'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><div class='subclass'> &gt; <strong>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</strong></div></div></div><div class='doc-contents'><p>An alert dialog is a modal view that includes an optional title, a message and buttons, \npositioned in the middle of the display.</p>\n\n<p><table id=\"platformComparison\">\n  <tr>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_android.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_ios.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n    <td><img src=\"images/alertdialog/alertdialog_mobileweb.png\" height=\"75\" /></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr><th>Android</th><th>iOS</th><th>Mobile Web</th></tr>\n</table>\n\n\n\n\n<p>An alert dialog is created using <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI-method-createAlertDialog\" rel=\"Titanium.UI-method-createAlertDialog\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.createAlertDialog</a> or <strong><code>&lt;AlertDialog&gt;</code></strong> Alloy element.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Although this dialog always appears in the middle of the display (not touching the edges), \nother aspects of its aesthetics and the way the user interacts with it are different for each \nplatform, as described below.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Android</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On Android, the default alert dialog displays text information, via a title and message, without \nany buttons. As the user can use the system hardware <code>back</code> button to dismiss it, a button is \noptional.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Buttons are shown if the <code>buttonNames</code> property is defined, and are rendered horizontally below \nthe message.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>To create a custom layout, a view may be added and, in turn, a hierarchy of views added to that \nchild view.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>iOS</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On iOS, the default alert dialog displays text information, via a title and message, with \na single button to allow it to be dismissed.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Buttons are defined using the <code>buttonNames</code> property and are rendered vertically below \nthe message.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On iOS 4.0 and later, alert dialogs are automatically cancelled when the application is \npaused/suspended. This behavior can avoided by setting <code>persistent</code> property on alert dialog \nto be <code>true</code>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On iOS 5.0 and later, <code>style</code> property can be used to allow the user to enter plain text, \nobscured text or login identifier and password. Entered values can be captured with listening\n<code>cancel</code> event.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Global Alias</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>A global method <code>alert()</code> is aliased to this object, and can be invoked with a single message. \nFor example</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>alert('this is a message');\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n\n<p>This will generate an alert with a title of \"Alert\" and an \"OK\" button.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Caveats</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Multiple alerts should not be shown at once.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <code>title</code> and <code>ok</code> properties cannot be changed while the alert dialog is being displayed. On\nAndroid only, you can change the <code>message</code> property while the alert dialog is being displayed.</p>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n<h3>Examples</h3>\n\n\n<h4>Single-button Alert Dialog (using alias)</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create a single-button alert dialog using the global <code>alert()</code> alias.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\n  exitOnClose: true,\n  fullscreen: false\n});\n\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  alert('The file has been deleted');\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Single-button Alert Dialog (standard)</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create a single-button alert dialog, without explicitly defining it using the <code>buttonNames</code> \nproperty, which is invoked when the app window is clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\nexitOnClose: true,\nfullscreen: false\n});\n\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    message: 'The file has been deleted',\n    ok: 'Okay',\n    title: 'File Deleted'\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Three-button Alert Dialog</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create a three-button alert dialog, which is invoked when the app window is clicked. \nOutput a message to the log when the cancel button is clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({  \n  title: 'Click window to test',\n  backgroundColor: 'white',\n  exitOnClose: true,\n  fullscreen: false\n});\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    cancel: 1,\n    buttonNames: ['Confirm', 'Cancel', 'Help'],\n    message: 'Would you like to delete the file?',\n    title: 'Delete'\n  });\n  dialog.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n    if (e.index === e.source.cancel){\n      Ti.API.info('The cancel button was clicked');\n    }\n    Ti.API.info('e.cancel: ' + e.cancel);\n    Ti.API.info('e.source.cancel: ' + e.source.cancel);\n    Ti.API.info('e.index: ' + e.index);\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Alert Dialog with Plain Text Input (iOS 5 and later)</h4>\n\n\n<p>Create an alert dialog and allow the user enter plain text, which is invoked when the\napp window is clicked.\nOutput entered text value to the log when the OK button is clicked.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>Ti.UI.setBackgroundColor('white');\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow({\n  title: 'Click window to test'\n});\nwin.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n  var dialog = Ti.UI.createAlertDialog({\n    title: 'Enter text',\n    style: Ti.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.PLAIN_TEXT_INPUT,\n    buttonNames: ['OK']\n  });\n  dialog.addEventListener('click', function(e){\n    Ti.API.info('e.text: ' + e.text);\n  });\n  dialog.show();\n});\nwin.open();\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Alloy XML Markup</h4>\n\n\n<p>Previous three-button alert dialog example as an Alloy view.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>alertdialog.xml:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Alloy&gt;\n    &lt;Window id=\"win\" onClick=\"showDialog\" title=\"Click window to test\" backgroundColor=\"white\"\n        exitOnClose=\"true\" fullscreen=\"false\" &gt;\n\n        &lt;AlertDialog id=\"dialog\" onClick=\"doClick\" title=\"Delete\"\n            message=\"Would you like to delete the file?\" cancel=\"1\"&gt;\n\n            &lt;!-- The ButtonNames tag sets the buttonNames property. --&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonNames&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Confirm&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Cancel&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n                &lt;ButtonName&gt;Help&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;/ButtonNames&gt;\n        &lt;/AlertDialog&gt;\n    &lt;/Window&gt;\n&lt;/Alloy&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n\n<p>alertdialog.js:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>function showDialog(){\n    $.dialog.show();\n};\n\nfunction doClick(e){\n    Ti.API.info('e.text: ' + e.text);\n};\n</code></pre>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li></ul></div><div class='members'><div class='members-section'><div class='definedBy'>Defined By</div><h3 class='members-title icon-property'>Properties</h3><div class='subsection'><div id='property-androidView' class='member first-child not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-androidView' class='name not-expandable'>androidView</a><span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.View\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.View\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.View</a></span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>View to load inside the message area, to create a custom layout.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>View to load inside the message area, to create a custom layout.</p>\n\n<p><p>In an Alloy application you can specify this property with either an <code>&lt;AndroidView/&gt;</code> or\n<code>&lt;View/&gt;</code> element inside the <code>&lt;AlertDialog/&gt;</code> element, for example:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Alloy&gt;\n    &lt;AlertDialog onClick=\"doClick\" title=\"Delete\"\n        message=\"Would you like to delete the file?\" cancel=\"1\"&gt;\n\n        &lt;!--  Add View or AndroidView for the androidView property  --&gt;\n        &lt;View platform=\"android\"&gt;\n            &lt;Label color=\"red\" text=\"Warning!  This change is permanent and you cannot undo it!\" /&gt;\n        &lt;/View&gt;\n\n        &lt;ButtonNames&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Confirm&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Cancel&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n        &lt;/ButtonNames&gt;\n    &lt;/AlertDialog&gt;\n&lt;/Alloy&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-apiName' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-apiName' class='name not-expandable'>apiName</a><span> : String</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to.</p>\n\n<p><p>The value of this property is the fully qualified name of the API. For example, <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Button\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Button\" class=\"docClass\">Button</a>\nreturns <code>Ti.UI.Button</code>.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>3.2.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-bubbleParent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent' class='name expandable'>bubbleParent</a><span> : Boolean</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent.</p>\n\n<p><p>Some proxies (most commonly views) have a relationship to other proxies, often\nestablished by the add() method. For example, for a button added to a window, a\nclick event on the button would bubble up to the window. Other common parents are\ntable sections to their rows, table views to their sections, and scrollable views\nto their views. Set this property to false to disable the bubbling to the proxy's parent.</p>\n\n</p><p>Default: true</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-buttonNames' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-buttonNames' class='name expandable'>buttonNames</a><span> : String[]</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Name of each button to create. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Name of each button to create.</p>\n\n<p><p>On iOS, a button will automatically be created if none are explicitly defined, because \nwithout it users would be unable to dismiss the dialog. Conversely, a dialog with no \nbuttons may be created on Android, as the hardware <code>back</code> button may be used instead.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>A maximum of 3 buttons is supported on Android.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Alloy applications can specify this property with a <code>&lt;ButtonNames&gt;</code> element containing\none or more <code>&lt;ButtonName&gt;</code> elements (see example).</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Alloy&gt;\n    &lt;AlertDialog id=\"dialog\" onClick=\"doClick\" title=\"Decide!\" message=\"Do you really want to do that?\" cancel=\"1\"&gt;\n        &lt;ButtonNames&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Confirm&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Cancel&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n            &lt;ButtonName&gt;Help&lt;/ButtonName&gt;\n        &lt;/ButtonNames&gt;\n    &lt;/AlertDialog&gt;\n&lt;/Alloy&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n</p><p>Default: No buttons (Android), Single \"OK\" button (iOS, Mobile Web)</p></div></div></div><div id='property-cancel' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-cancel' class='name expandable'>cancel</a><span> : Number</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Index to define the cancel button. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Index to define the cancel button.</p>\n\n<p><p>On iOS and Mobile Web, set to <code>-1</code> to disable the cancel option.</p>\n\n</p><p>Default: undefined (Android), -1 (iOS, Mobile Web)</p></div></div></div><div id='property-destructive' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-destructive' class='name expandable'>destructive</a><span> : Number</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Index to define the destructive button. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Index to define the destructive button.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p> <b>Requires:</b> \niOS 8.0 and later \n</p>\n\n<p><p>Note that this property is only available on iOS 8 or above. Setting to -1 disables this option.</p>\n\n</p><p>Default: -1</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.5.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.5.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-lifecycleContainer' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer' class='name not-expandable'>lifecycleContainer</a><span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a></span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy.</p>\n\n<p><p>If this property is set to a Window or TabGroup, then the corresponding Activity lifecycle event callbacks\nwill also be called on the proxy. Proxies that require the activity lifecycle will need this property set\nto the appropriate containing Window or TabGroup.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.6.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-message' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-message' class='name not-expandable'>message</a><span> : String</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Dialog message.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Dialog message.</p>\n\n</div></div></div><div id='property-messageid' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-messageid' class='name not-expandable'>messageid</a><span> : String</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Key identifying a string in the locale file to use for the message text.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Key identifying a string in the locale file to use for the message text.</p>\n\n</div></div></div><div id='property-ok' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-ok' class='name not-expandable'>ok</a><span> : String</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Text for the <code>OK</code> button.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Text for the <code>OK</code> button.</p>\n\n<p><p>This property is useful when only one button is required, as it negates the need to define \nthe <code>buttonNames</code> property. If <code>buttonNames</code> is defined, this property is ignored.</p>\n\n</p></div></div></div><div id='property-okid' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-okid' class='name not-expandable'>okid</a><span> : String</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Key identifying a string in the locale file to use for the <code>ok</code> text.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Key identifying a string in the locale file to use for the <code>ok</code> text.</p>\n\n<p><p>If <code>buttonNames</code> is defined, this property is ignored.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-persistent' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-persistent' class='name expandable'>persistent</a><span> : Boolean</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Boolean value indicating if the alert dialog should only be cancelled by user gesture or by hide method. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Boolean value indicating if the alert dialog should only be cancelled by user gesture or by hide method.</p>\n\n<p><p>This property is useful to ensure that the alert dialog will not be ignored \nby the user when the application is paused/suspended.</p>\n\n</p><p>Default: false on iOS, true on Android</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-style' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-style' class='name expandable'>style</a><span> : Number</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>The style for the alert dialog. ...</div><div class='long'><p>The style for the alert dialog.</p>\n\n<p><p>Style of the alert dialog, specified using one of the constants from\n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle</a>. Using styles other than default one can break\nyour dialog layout if more than two buttons used. All styles can handle up to two\nbuttons comfortably, except for default style can handle up to six buttons when <code>title</code>\nand <code>message</code> is empty or not given. Note that this property is only available on\niOS SDK 5 or above. </p>\n\n</p><p>Default: <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-DEFAULT\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-DEFAULT\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.DEFAULT</a></p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-title' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-title' class='name not-expandable'>title</a><span> : String</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Title of the dialog.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Title of the dialog.</p>\n\n<p><p>If not set, a dialog with no title bar will be created.</p>\n\n</p></div></div></div><div id='property-titleid' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-titleid' class='name not-expandable'>titleid</a><span> : String</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Key identifying a string in the locale file to use for the title text.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Key identifying a string in the locale file to use for the title text.</p>\n\n</div></div></div></div></div><div class='members-section'><div class='definedBy'>Defined By</div><h3 class='members-title icon-method'>Methods</h3><div class='subsection'><div id='method-addEventListener' class='member first-child inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-addEventListener' class='name expandable'>addEventListener</a>( <span class='pre'>name, callback</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Adds the specified callback as an event listener for the named event. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Adds the specified callback as an event listener for the named event.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>name</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Name of the event.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>callback</span> : Callback&lt;Object&gt;<div class='sub-desc'><p>Callback function to invoke when the event is fired.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-applyProperties' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-applyProperties' class='name expandable'>applyProperties</a>( <span class='pre'>props</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Applies the properties to the proxy. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Applies the properties to the proxy.</p>\n\n<p><p>Properties are supplied as a dictionary. Each key-value pair in the object is applied to the proxy such that\nmyproxy[key] = value.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>3.0.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>props</span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Dictionary\" rel=\"Dictionary\" class=\"docClass\">Dictionary</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>A dictionary of properties to apply.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-fireEvent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-fireEvent' class='name expandable'>fireEvent</a>( <span class='pre'>name, event</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Fires a synthesized event to any registered listeners. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Fires a synthesized event to any registered listeners.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>name</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Name of the event.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>event</span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Dictionary\" rel=\"Dictionary\" class=\"docClass\">Dictionary</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>A dictionary of keys and values to add to the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Event\" rel=\"Titanium.Event\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Event</a> object sent to the listeners.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getApiName' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-getApiName' class='name expandable'>getApiName</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the apiName property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-apiName\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-apiName\" class=\"docClass\">apiName</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>3.2.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getBubbleParent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-getBubbleParent' class='name expandable'>getBubbleParent</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the bubbleParent property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" class=\"docClass\">bubbleParent</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getButtonNames' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getButtonNames' class='name expandable'>getButtonNames</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String[]</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the buttonNames property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-buttonNames\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-buttonNames\" class=\"docClass\">buttonNames</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String[]</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getCancel' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getCancel' class='name expandable'>getCancel</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Number</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the cancel property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-cancel\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-cancel\" class=\"docClass\">cancel</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Number</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getDestructive' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getDestructive' class='name expandable'>getDestructive</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Number</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the destructive property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-destructive\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-destructive\" class=\"docClass\">destructive</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.5.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.5.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Number</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getLifecycleContainer' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-getLifecycleContainer' class='name expandable'>getLifecycleContainer</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the lifecycleContainer property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" class=\"docClass\">lifecycleContainer</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.6.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'><a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a></span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getMessage' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getMessage' class='name expandable'>getMessage</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the message property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-message\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-message\" class=\"docClass\">message</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getOk' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getOk' class='name expandable'>getOk</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the ok property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-ok\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-ok\" class=\"docClass\">ok</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getPersistent' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getPersistent' class='name expandable'>getPersistent</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the persistent property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-persistent\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-persistent\" class=\"docClass\">persistent</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getStyle' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getStyle' class='name expandable'>getStyle</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Number</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the style property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-style\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-style\" class=\"docClass\">style</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Number</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getTitle' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-getTitle' class='name expandable'>getTitle</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the title property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-title\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-title\" class=\"docClass\">title</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-hide' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-hide' class='name expandable'>hide</a>( <span class='pre'></span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Hides this dialog. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Hides this dialog.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-removeEventListener' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-removeEventListener' class='name expandable'>removeEventListener</a>( <span class='pre'>name, callback</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event.</p>\n\n<p><p>Multiple listeners can be registered for the same event, so the \n<code>callback</code> parameter is used to determine which listener to remove. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>When adding a listener, you must save a reference to the callback function\nin order to remove the listener later:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>var listener = function() { Ti.API.info(\"Event listener called.\"); }\nwindow.addEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n\n<p>To remove the listener, pass in a reference to the callback function:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>window.removeEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>\n\n</p><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>name</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Name of the event.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>callback</span> : Callback&lt;Object&gt;<div class='sub-desc'><p>Callback function to remove. Must be the same function passed to <code>addEventListener</code>.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setBubbleParent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-setBubbleParent' class='name expandable'>setBubbleParent</a>( <span class='pre'>bubbleParent</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the bubbleParent property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" class=\"docClass\">bubbleParent</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>bubbleParent</span> : Boolean<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setButtonNames' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setButtonNames' class='name expandable'>setButtonNames</a>( <span class='pre'>buttonNames</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the buttonNames property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-buttonNames\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-buttonNames\" class=\"docClass\">buttonNames</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>buttonNames</span> : Array&lt;String&gt;<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setCancel' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setCancel' class='name expandable'>setCancel</a>( <span class='pre'>cancel</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the cancel property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-cancel\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-cancel\" class=\"docClass\">cancel</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>cancel</span> : Number<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setDestructive' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setDestructive' class='name expandable'>setDestructive</a>( <span class='pre'>destructive</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the destructive property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-destructive\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-destructive\" class=\"docClass\">destructive</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.5.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.5.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>destructive</span> : Number<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setLifecycleContainer' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-setLifecycleContainer' class='name expandable'>setLifecycleContainer</a>( <span class='pre'>lifecycleContainer</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the lifecycleContainer property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" class=\"docClass\">lifecycleContainer</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.6.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>lifecycleContainer</span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setMessage' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setMessage' class='name expandable'>setMessage</a>( <span class='pre'>message</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the message property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-message\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-message\" class=\"docClass\">message</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>message</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setOk' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setOk' class='name expandable'>setOk</a>( <span class='pre'>ok</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the ok property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-ok\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-ok\" class=\"docClass\">ok</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>ok</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setPersistent' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setPersistent' class='name expandable'>setPersistent</a>( <span class='pre'>persistent</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the persistent property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-persistent\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-persistent\" class=\"docClass\">persistent</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>persistent</span> : Boolean<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setStyle' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setStyle' class='name expandable'>setStyle</a>( <span class='pre'>style</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the style property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-style\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-style\" class=\"docClass\">style</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>style</span> : Number<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setTitle' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-setTitle' class='name expandable'>setTitle</a>( <span class='pre'>title</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the title property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-title\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-title\" class=\"docClass\">title</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>title</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-show' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-method-show' class='name expandable'>show</a>( <span class='pre'></span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Shows this dialog. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Shows this dialog.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div class='members-section'><div class='definedBy'>Defined By</div><h3 class='members-title icon-event'>Events</h3><div class='subsection'><div id='event-click' class='member first-child not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.UI.AlertDialog'>Titanium.UI.AlertDialog</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-event-click' class='name expandable'>click</a></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Fired when a button in the dialog is clicked. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Fired when a button in the dialog is clicked.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Properties</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>cancel</span> : Boolean/Number<div class='sub-desc'><p>Boolean type on Android and Mobile Web; Number on iOS. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On Android and Mobile Web, indicates whether the cancel button was clicked, in which \ncase returns <code>true</code>. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On iOS, the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-cancel\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.AlertDialog-property-cancel\" class=\"docClass\">cancel</a> property is \nreturned, if defined, or <code>-1</code> otherwise. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>See the <code>Three-button Alert Dialog</code> example for a cross-platform workaround for this \nparity issue.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>index</span> : Number<div class='sub-desc'><p>Index of the button that was clicked.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>login</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Value of login field if dialog <code>style</code> property is defined as \n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-LOGIN_AND_PASSWORD_INPUT\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-LOGIN_AND_PASSWORD_INPUT\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.LOGIN_AND_PASSWORD_INPUT</a>.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"platforms\"><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad' >&nbsp;</li></ul></div></li><li><span class='pre'>password</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Value of password field if dialog <code>style</code> property is defined as \n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-LOGIN_AND_PASSWORD_INPUT\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-LOGIN_AND_PASSWORD_INPUT\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.LOGIN_AND_PASSWORD_INPUT</a>.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"platforms\"><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad' >&nbsp;</li></ul></div></li><li><span class='pre'>text</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Value of text field if dialog <code>style</code> property is defined as\n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-PLAIN_TEXT_INPUT\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-PLAIN_TEXT_INPUT\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.PLAIN_TEXT_INPUT</a> or \n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-SECURE_TEXT_INPUT\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle-property-SECURE_TEXT_INPUT\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.iPhone.AlertDialogStyle.SECURE_TEXT_INPUT</a>.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"platforms\"><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad' >&nbsp;</li></ul></div></li><li><span class='pre'>source</span> : Object<div class='sub-desc'><p>Source object that fired the event.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"platforms\"><li class='platform-android' title='Android' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad' >&nbsp;</li></ul></div></li><li><span class='pre'>type</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Name of the event fired.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"platforms\"><li class='platform-android' title='Android' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad' >&nbsp;</li></ul></div></li><li><span class='pre'>bubbles</span> : Boolean<div class='sub-desc'><p>True if the event will try to bubble up if possible.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"platforms\"><li class='platform-android' title='Android' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad' >&nbsp;</li></ul></div></li><li><span class='pre'>cancelBubble</span> : Boolean<div class='sub-desc'><p>Set to true to stop the event from bubbling.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"platforms\"><li class='platform-android' title='Android' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone' >&nbsp;</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad' >&nbsp;</li></ul></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>"});